{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "rdam-backend-2026",
    "name": "RDAM Backend — Sistema de Certificados Digitales",
    "description": "Coleccion completa de pruebas para RDAM Backend.\nIncluye autenticacion dual con OTP por email, FSM de solicitudes, pagos PlusPagos y certificados PDF.\n\nFlujo de uso:\n1. Ejecutar TC-01 (Login ciudadano) — envia OTP al email\n2. Copiar el codigo OTP del email y reemplazar en TC-01b\n3. Ejecutar TC-01b (Verify OTP) — captura JWT automaticamente\n4. Repetir con TC-02/TC-02b para el empleado interno\n5. Ejecutar el resto de los tests en orden secuencial\n\nLos scripts de Tests capturan automaticamente los tokens JWT y IDs de solicitud.\n\nAlumno: Alan Acevedo | Campus 2026\ni2T Software Factory",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url",              "value": "http://localhost:8080" },
    { "key": "token_ciudadano",       "value": "" },
    { "key": "token_interno",         "value": "" },
    { "key": "solicitud_id",          "value": "" },
    { "key": "solicitud_id_rechazo",  "value": "" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. Auth",
      "description": "Autenticacion dual con verificacion OTP por email.\nFlujo: POST /auth/login (solo username+password, sin campo tipo) -> OTP al email -> POST /auth/verify -> retorna { token }.\n\nNOTA: AuthResponse retorna solo el campo 'token'. No hay refreshToken en este flujo.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "TC-01 — Login ciudadano (envia OTP)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"20123456789\",\n  \"password\": \"rdam1234\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "login"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// TC-01: LoginRequest tiene solo username y password — sin campo 'tipo'",
                  "// AuthService detecta ciudadano/empleado automaticamente por CUIL vs legajo",
                  "pm.test('TC-01: Login ciudadano retorna 200 y mensaje OTP', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.message).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.not.have.property('token');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.not.have.property('accessToken');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "TC-01b — Verificar OTP ciudadano (obtiene JWT)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"TU_EMAIL@gmail.com\",\n  \"codigo\": \"REEMPLAZAR_CON_CODIGO_OTP\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/verify",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "verify"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// AuthResponse: { token: '...' } — solo el campo 'token', no accessToken ni refreshToken",
                  "pm.test('TC-01b: Verificacion OTP retorna JWT ciudadano', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.not.have.property('accessToken');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.not.have.property('refreshToken');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.not.have.property('rol');",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token_ciudadano', json.token);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "TC-02 — Login empleado interno (envia OTP)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"LEG001\",\n  \"password\": \"cualquier_valor\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "login"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// EmpleadoAuthProvider usa mock LDAP: acepta CUALQUIER password si el legajo existe en la DB",
                  "pm.test('TC-02: Login interno retorna 200 y mensaje OTP', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.message).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.not.have.property('token');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "TC-02b — Verificar OTP interno (obtiene JWT)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"REEMPLAZAR_CON_EMAIL_DEL_EMPLEADO\",\n  \"codigo\": \"REEMPLAZAR_CON_CODIGO_OTP\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/verify",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "verify"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('TC-02b: Verificacion OTP retorna JWT interno', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "    var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.not.have.property('accessToken');",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token_interno', json.token);",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "TC-03 — Login credenciales invalidas",
          "request": {
